securityGroupCheck()

Description
    bool securityGroupCheck(string $group [, array $userGroups = NULL])
	Determines whether the first parameter, $group, exists within the second, $userGroups.  If a second parameter is not specified, the first 	
	parameter is tested against the elements of the session variable, $_SESSION['groups'].

Parameters
    group
		The group to search.
    userGroups
		An array of user groups.  NULL by default.

Return Values
    Returns a boolean value of TRUE or FALSE.  Returns TRUE if the group name is found within the array of user groups.  Returns FALSE otherwise.
	
Examples

See Also
	securityOUCheck()
	securityUserCheck()